			<div class="block">
				
				<a href="/resources/"><strong class="page-tag">Resources</strong></a>
				
				<div class="post-title">
					<h2>Logos and guidelines</h2>
					<p>&nbsp;</p>
				</div>
				
					<p>We've put together a few different images and logos you can use for promoting festival events, writing about festival events, or whatever, really. Essentially they're free to use. We're putting them out under <a rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported License</a>. We'd put it out as public domain, but that's complicated in some jurisdictions. This license means that you're free to use them for any purpose, including commercial purposes, and to modify them as you like, so long as you provide attribution to us. And just the act of using any of the imagery constitutes attribution in and of itself - there's nothing else you need to do. </p>
				
			</div>
CONTENT_0
