				<div class="post-title">
					<h2>HTML/CSS logo code</h2>
					<p>&nbsp;</p>
				</div>
<form name="logocustomiser" id="logocustomiser">
<fieldset>
					<p>Use the code below and paste it into your website HTML to get a copy of our logo on your site like this (you can skip steps 1-3 if you can't save files to your website, but you won't get the full effect - you might want to download <a href="#imagelogo">one of the image versions</a> instead, then):</p>
					<ol>
					<li>Download the <a href="/rsc/04b19.zip">zip file with the fonts for the logo</a></li>
					<li>Unzip the fonts into a directory on your website</li>
					<li>Add the path of the directory into which you've unzipped the fonts into the "Font path" field (e.g. <em>/mycss/myfonts/</em>)<br /><br />
					            <label for="fontpath" class="flabel">Font path</label>
            <input type=text class=text-input name="fontpath" id="fontpath" onchange="updateFontPath();"/></li>
					<li>Adjust the size of the logo using the bigger/smaller buttons<br />
					<a href="javascript:embiggen()" class="btn more" id="embiggen">Bigger</a> <a href="javascript:emsmallen()" class="btn less"  id="emsmallen">Smaller</a></li>
					
     <p>&nbsp;</p>
						<h2 class="ldflogo" id="eg">Leeds Digital Festival</h2>
			<li>Copy the code below and add it to your website<br /><br />
						<label for=logocode>Logo code</label>
            <textarea rows=10 cols=50 id="logocode"></textarea>	</li>
					</ol>
</fieldset>
</form>
